modules.description: Provides functions for accurate probabilistic branching using exact arithmetic, avoiding floating-point inaccuracies. Operates on probabilities represented as rational numbers and generates execution paths based on precise comparisons. Used in randomized algorithms requiring strict correctness guarantees, such as cryptographic protocols or formal verification systems.

Provides operations to process and transform a sequence of numerical samples, including sliding window aggregation and exponential smoothing. Works with streams of float values and maintains internal state between calls. Used to analyze real-time sensor data for trend detection and anomaly identification.
